@page "/docs/arrows"

<PageTitle>Arrow System - Tldraw.Blazor Docs</PageTitle>

<div class="docs-content">
    <h1>Arrow System</h1>
    <p class="docs-lead">Create arrows with auto-binding endpoints that snap to shapes and follow them when moved.</p>

    <h2 id="creating">
        Creating Arrows
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#creating">#</a>
    </h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Press <kbd>A</kbd> to activate Arrow tool</li>
        <li>Drag from start point to end point</li>
        <li>If endpoints are near shapes, they auto-bind (green dot)</li>
        <li>Release to create the arrow</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="bindings">
        Bindings
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#bindings">#</a>
    </h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Green dot</strong> — endpoint is bound to a shape</li>
        <li><strong>Blue dot</strong> — endpoint is unbound</li>
        <li>When a bound shape moves, the arrow endpoint follows automatically</li>
        <li>Bindings are stored as <code>TLBindingRecord</code> in the store</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="editing">
        Editing Endpoints
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#editing">#</a>
    </h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Switch to Select tool (<kbd>V</kbd>)</li>
        <li>Click on an arrow endpoint dot</li>
        <li>Drag to move the endpoint</li>
        <li>Release near a shape to rebind</li>
        <li>Press <kbd>Escape</kbd> to cancel</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="api">
        Arrow API
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#api">#</a>
    </h2>

    <CodeBlock Language="csharp" Code="@(@"// Create arrow
var arrow = editor.CreateShape(""arrow"", 100, 100);

// Try binding endpoint
editor.TryBindArrowEndpoint(arrow.Id, ""start"", 150, 150);
editor.TryBindArrowEndpoint(arrow.Id, ""end"", 400, 300);

// Get binding
var binding = editor.GetArrowBinding(arrow.Id, ""start"");

// Remove binding
editor.UnbindArrowEndpoint(arrow.Id, ""start"");

// Update all bindings (call after moving shapes)
editor.UpdateAllArrowBindings();")" />
</div>
